  "prompt": "What is a type of energy?",
  "response": "There are many types of energy, but here are some of the most common ones:\n\n1. **Kinetic Energy**: The energy of an object in motion. It depends on the mass and speed of the object.\n\n2. **Potential Energy**: The energy stored in an object due to its position or configuration. It includes gravitational potential energy (due to an object's height) and elastic potential energy (stored in stretched or compressed materials).\n\n3. **Thermal Energy**: The energy related to the temperature of an object, arising from the kinetic energy of its particles. It is often associated with heat.\n\n4. **Chemical Energy**: The energy stored in the bonds of chemical compounds, which can be released during a chemical reaction.\n\n5. **Electrical Energy**: The energy created by the movement of electrons. This type of energy powers electronic devices and systems.\n\n6. **Nuclear Energy**: The energy stored in the nucleus of atoms, which can be released during nuclear reactions (fission or fusion).\n\n7. **Radiant Energy**: The energy of electromagnetic waves, including visible light, radio waves, and X-rays.\n\n8. **Mechanical Energy**: The sum of kinetic and potential energy in a system, often used in the context of machines and physical systems.\n\nEach type of energy has its unique properties and applications across various fields of science and engineering.",
